    {
        "title": "Vue.js Editor",
        "content": "<h1>Vue.js Code Editor</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\" disabled>❮ Home</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Interactive Vue.js Playground</h3><p class=\"text-block\">Practice Vue.js code directly in your browser! This editor simulates a full Vue 3 development environment with Composition API, Vue Router, Pinia state management, and component architecture.</p><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 0; font-size: 18px; padding: 15px 30px;\" onclick=\"window.open('editor/vue-editor.html', '_blank')\">🚀 Open Vue.js Editor</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>What You Can Practice</h3><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li><strong>Composition API</strong> - Modern reactivity with setup()</li><li><strong>Components</strong> - Reusable UI with props/events</li><li><strong>Reactivity</strong> - ref(), reactive(), computed()</li><li><strong>Router</strong> - Vue Router navigation</li><li><strong>State Management</strong> - Pinia stores</li><li><strong>Directives</strong> - v-if, v-for, v-model</li></ul></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Pro Tips</h3><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Use <strong>Ctrl + Enter</strong> (or Cmd + Enter on Mac) to quickly run your code</li><li>Your code is automatically saved</li><li>Editor supports Vue 3.4+ with Composition API</li></ul></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\" disabled>❮ Home</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Vue.js Introduction",
        "content": "<h1>Vue.js Introduction</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\" disabled>❮ Home</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>The Progressive JavaScript Framework</h3><p class=\"text-block\">Vue.js (pronounced /vjuː/, like 'view') is a progressive framework for building user interfaces. Unlike other monolithic frameworks, Vue is designed from the ground up to be incrementally adoptable.</p></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Why Vue.js?</h3><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li><strong>Versatile:</strong> Use for small widgets or full SPAs</li><li><strong>Performant:</strong> Virtual DOM + reactivity system</li><li><strong>Developer Friendly:</strong> Gentle learning curve</li><li><strong>Modern:</strong> Vue 3 with Composition API</li></ul></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\" disabled>❮ Home</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Vue.js Installation",
        "content": "<h1>Vue.js Installation</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Create Vue App</h3><p class=\"text-block\">Use Vite (recommended) or Vue CLI to scaffold a new Vue 3 project with TypeScript and modern tooling.</p></div><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">Terminal Commands (Vite)</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre>npm create vue@latest my-vue-app -- --typescript\ncd my-vue-app\nnpm install\nnpm run dev</pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">Vue CLI Alternative</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre>npm install -g @vue/cli\nvue create my-vue-app\ncd my-vue-app\nnpm run serve</pre></div></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Composition API Basics",
        "content": "<h1>Composition API (Vue 3)</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>The New Standard</h3><p class=\"text-block\">Composition API is the modern way to organize component logic. It replaces Options API and enables better TypeScript support and code reuse.</p></div><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">setup() Function</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><script setup>\nimport { ref } from 'vue'\n\nconst count = ref(0)\n\nfunction increment() {\n  count.value++\n}\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <h1>{{ count }}</h1>\n  <button @click=\"increment\">+1</button>\n</template></pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Reactivity Fundamentals",
        "content": "<h1>Reactivity Core</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>ref vs reactive</h3><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">ref() - Primitives</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre>import { ref, computed } from 'vue'\n\nconst count = ref(0)\nconst double = computed(() => count.value * 2)\n\nconst name = ref('Vue')\n\n// Access with .value\nconst display = computed(() => `${name.value} ${count.value}`)</pre></div></div><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">reactive() - Objects</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre>const state = reactive({\n  count: 0,\n  name: 'Vue'\n})\n\n// No .value needed\nstate.count++</pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Vue Components",
        "content": "<h1>Components & Props</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">Parent Component</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><script setup>\nimport MyButton from './MyButton.vue'\n\nconst count = ref(0)\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <MyButton :count=\"count\" @update=\"count = $event\" />\n</template></pre></div></div><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">MyButton.vue</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><script setup>\nconst props = defineProps({\n  count: Number\n})\n\nconst emit = defineEmits(['update'])\n\nfunction increment() {\n  emit('update', props.count + 1)\n}\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <button @click=\"increment\">\n    Count is {{ props.count }}\n  </button>\n</template></pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Vue Directives",
        "content": "<h1>Built-in Directives</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Control Flow</h3><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">v-if / v-show / v-for</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><template>\n  <div v-if=\"isLoggedIn\">Welcome!</div>\n  <div v-show=\"showMenu\">Menu</div>\n  \n  <li v-for=\"item in items\" :key=\"item.id\">\n    {{ item.name }}\n  </li>\n</template>\n\n<script setup>\nconst isLoggedIn = ref(false)\nconst showMenu = ref(true)\nconst items = ref([{id:1, name:'Vue'}])\n</script></pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>v-model</h3><p class=\"text-block\">Two-way binding for forms.</p></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Vue Router",
        "content": "<h1>Vue Router</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Client-side Routing</h3><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">router/index.js</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre>import { createRouter, createWebHistory } from 'vue-router'\nimport Home from '../views/Home.vue'\n\nconst router = createRouter({\n  history: createWebHistory(),\n  routes: [\n    { path: '/', component: Home },\n    { path: '/about', component: About }\n  ]\n})\n\nexport default router</pre></div></div><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">App.vue</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><script setup>\nimport { RouterView } from 'vue-router'\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <RouterView />\n  <nav>\n    <RouterLink to=\"/\">Home</RouterLink>\n  </nav>\n</template></pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Pinia State Management",
        "content": "<h1>Pinia - Modern State</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Official Vue 3 Store</h3><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">stores/counter.js</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre>import { defineStore } from 'pinia'\nimport { ref } from 'vue'\n\nexport const useCounterStore = defineStore('counter', () => {\n  const count = ref(0)\n  \n  function increment() {\n    count.value++\n  }\n  \n  return { count, increment }\n})</pre></div></div><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">Component Usage</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><script setup>\nimport { useCounterStore } from '../stores/counter'\n\nconst store = useCounterStore()\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <p>{{ store.count }}</p>\n  <button @click=\"store.increment\">+1</button>\n</template></pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Lifecycle Hooks",
        "content": "<h1>Component Lifecycle</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">Lifecycle Hooks</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><script setup>\nimport { onMounted, onUnmounted, onUpdated } from 'vue'\n\nconst message = ref('')\n\nonMounted(() => {\n  console.log('Component mounted!')\n})\n\nonUpdated(() => {\n  console.log('Component updated')\n})\n\nonUnmounted(() => {\n  console.log('Component unmounted')\n})\n</script></pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Common Hooks</h3><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li><strong>onMounted</strong> - After initial render</li><li><strong>onUpdated</strong> - After reactivity update</li><li><strong>onUnmounted</strong> - Before destruction</li><li><strong>onBeforeMount</strong> - Before initial render</li></ul></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Template Refs",
        "content": "<h1>Template Refs & DOM Access</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">ref on Element</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><script setup>\nimport { ref, onMounted } from 'vue'\n\nconst inputRef = ref(null)\n\nonMounted(() => {\n  inputRef.value?.focus()\n})\n\nfunction clearInput() {\n  inputRef.value.value = ''\n}\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <input ref=\"inputRef\" />\n  <button @click=\"clearInput\">Clear</button>\n</template></pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>ref on Component</h3><p class=\"text-block\">Access child component methods.</p></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Provide/Inject",
        "content": "<h1>Provide / Inject</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Dependency Injection</h3><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">Ancestor Component</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><script setup>\nimport { provide } from 'vue'\n\nprovide('theme', 'dark')\nprovide('user', ref({ name: 'Vue' }))\n</script></pre></div></div><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">Descendant Component</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><script setup>\nimport { inject } from 'vue'\n\nconst theme = inject('theme', 'light')\nconst user = inject('user')\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  Theme: {{ theme }} - {{ user.name }}\n</template></pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Teleport & Suspense",
        "content": "<h1>Teleport & Suspense</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Teleport</h3><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">Portal-like</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><Teleport to=\"body\">\n  <div class=\"modal-overlay\">\n    Modal Content\n  </div>\n</Teleport></pre></div></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Suspense</h3><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">Async Components</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><Suspense>\n  <template #fallback>\n    Loading...\n  </template>\n  \n  <AsyncComponent />\n</Suspense></pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "TypeScript Support",
        "content": "<h1>TypeScript in Vue</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">Typed Props</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre><script setup lang=\"ts\">\ninterface Props {\n  count: number\n  name: string\n}\n\nconst props = withDefaults(defineProps<Props>(), {\n  name: 'Vue'\n})\n</script></pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Benefits</h3><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Full type checking</li><li>IntelliSense</li><li>Refactor safety</li></ul></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Build & Deploy",
        "content": "<h1>Production Build</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Vite Build</h3><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">Commands</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre>npm run build  # Creates /dist folder\nnpm run preview # Local production preview</pre></div></div><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">vite.config.js</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre>import { defineConfig } from 'vite'\nimport vue from '@vitejs/plugin-vue'\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  plugins: [vue()],\n  base: '/my-vue-app/',\n  build: {\n    sourcemap: true\n  }\n})</pre></div></div><br><button class=\"btn-try-it\" style=\"margin: 0 0 15px 15px;\">Try it Yourself »</button><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Deploy Options</h3><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Netlify/Vercel (drag & drop)</li><li>GitHub Pages</li><li>Traditional servers</li></ul></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Vue.js Best Practices",
        "content": "<h1>Vue.js Best Practices</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Folder Structure</h3><div class=\"syntax-wrapper\"><div class=\"syntax-header\">Recommended</div><div class=\"code-editor\"><pre>src/\n  components/    # Reusable UI\n  views/         # Route pages\n  composables/   # Custom hooks\n  stores/        # Pinia stores\n  router/\n  assets/</pre></div></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Rules</h3><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Prefer Composition API</li><li>Single file components</li><li>TypeScript for scale</li><li>Pinia > Vuex</li></ul></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\">Next ❯</button></div>"
    },
    {
        "title": "Vue.js Summary",
        "content": "<h1>Vue.js Course Summary</h1><div class=\"page-nav-buttons\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\" disabled>Next ❯</button></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>You Did It!</h3><p class=\"text-block\">Congratulations on completing Vue.js!</p><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li><strong>Composition API:</strong> Modern reactivity system</li><li><strong>Components:</strong> Reusable with props/events</li><li><strong>Router:</strong> Client-side navigation</li><li><strong>Pinia:</strong> TypeScript-first state management</li><li><strong>Performance:</strong> Vite + Tree-shaking</li></ul></div><div class=\"content-section\"><h3>Next Steps</h3><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Build a multi-page app (Todo + Router)</li><li>Integrate with Nuxt 3 (SSR)</li><li>Learn VueUse composables</li><li>Explore server components</li></ul></div><div class=\"content-section\"><p class=\"text-block\" style=\"font-size: 18px; color: #00ffb3; font-weight: bold;\">Keep building with Vue!</p></div><div class=\"page-nav-buttons bottom-nav\"><button class=\"btn-secondary prev-btn\">❮ Previous</button><button class=\"btn-primary next-btn\" disabled>Next ❯</button></div>"
